reviewText: The brat pack favourites.  The Breakfast Club starring 5 teenagers that all hang out in different social circles and have to spend a Saturday in detention together for various reasons.  Once they start talking and getting to know one another, they realize that they are not so different after all.Sixteen Candles - as a teenage girl I too loved Jake Ryan.  Molly Ringwald is in love with him too, but does he know she exists?  With all of the commotion going on with relatives in town for her sister's wedding, her parents even forget her birthday!  Are her and Jake meant to be?  I think most of you know.  And everyone loves Long Duck Dong.Fast Times at Ridgemont High- This is a definite coming of age film.  Learning about sex, love, and growing up.
summary: Perfect purchase if you grew up with these movies

reviewText: The only thing that would have made this collection better would have been if Pretty In Pink was there instead of Fast Times. But, still, a terrific buy! reviewText: I bought this for The Breakfast Club and Sixteen Candles but Fast Times At Ridgemont High is a nice to have film,  These films are family favorites.  I adore Molly Ringwald anyhow so I would have bought it for the  ones she is in.  The Breakfast Club is about detention becoming a rite of passage.  Sixteen Candles is a coming of age film and the problems a teenage girl has on her sixteenth birthday.  A word to wise parents, the sixteenth birthday of ANY TEEN, male or female, is a big deal.  DON'T MESS UP THEIR MEMORIES!  FT@RH is about a study of teens discovering and avoiding the temptations all teens must endure -- Sex, drugs and the negative lure of rock-n-roll!  This is a wonderful collection.  I had no problems with it, though I have read of others who did.  They are subtitled  in English for the deaf.
